                            <comment id="433906" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 06:30:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56693/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56693/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18341&quot; title=&quot;interop: sanity-flr test_36: FAIL: write finished before layout version is transmitted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18341&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18341&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: skip sanity-flr/test_36 for new servers&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: b2_15&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 1bd798187c2ea806a6d0abe853ad22b55326fe42&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433254" author="adilger" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2024 00:26:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be worthwhile to implement &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18356&quot; title=&quot;test-framework to fetch except list from server for interop testing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18356&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18356&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and get this landed on both master and b2_15.  After that, it would be possible to land a patch on &lt;b&gt;master&lt;/b&gt; to skip a subtest being run from a b2_15 &lt;b&gt;client&lt;/b&gt;.  That avoids the need to land a patch on the older branch in order to skip a subtest that is broken by a change in the newer code, like in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433070" author="yujian" created="Mon, 28 Oct 2024 22:46:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.15.5 client with 2.16.0.RC5 server:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/421d679b-262d-4c77-9e03-076dcb68d961&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/421d679b-262d-4c77-9e03-076dcb68d961&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431481" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 15 Oct 2024 11:02:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Zhenyu Xu &amp;lt;bobijam@hotmail.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56693&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56693&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18341&quot; title=&quot;interop: sanity-flr test_36: FAIL: write finished before layout version is transmitted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18341&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18341&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: skip sanity-flr/test_36 for new servers&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: b2_15&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 75edc7881a10268c1e76a49791bbc59d50c125a5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431333" author="pjones" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2024 13:35:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We always support both options. While I agree that it is the more common option for people to run with older servers and newer clients, it does still happen the other way round - if some clients cannot be upgraded to newer OS versions , say. Given that you seem to understand the reason for the test failure, can you please push a patch to avoid it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431319" author="bobijam" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2024 10:07:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m wondering why interop test between old clients and new servers is needed? Doesn&apos;t interop test usually happen between new clients and old servers as system upgrade usually changes clients before updating servers?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431247" author="bobijam" created="Sat, 12 Oct 2024 15:38:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14642&quot; title=&quot;transfer layout version to OST objects in layout change&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14642&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14642&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has changed server&apos;s behavior (2.16.0) which accept layout version change from client, which 2.15.5 client unexpected, which causes this interop test failure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431236" author="lixi_wc" created="Sat, 12 Oct 2024 14:15:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bobijam&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bobijam&quot;&gt;bobijam&lt;/a&gt; Would you please check this too?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430977" author="yujian" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2024 18:29:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The failure occurred consistently in the following 2.15.5 clients with 2.16.0 servers interop test sessions:&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-reviews_el8.10-x86_64_full-dne-part-1&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-reviews_el9.4-x86_64_full-dne-part-1&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-reviews_el9.4-x86_64_sles15sp5-x86_64_full-dne-part-1&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-reviews_el9.4-x86_64_ubuntu2204-x86_64_full-dne-part-1&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
